title: College football | Ohio roundup: Ely bounces back, throws five TDs to help Toledo rally
text:
No. 19 Toledo 51, Massachusetts 35: Phillip Ely recovered from a poor start and threw four of his five touchdown passes in the second half, and Toledo stormed back from an 18-point deficit for a win over Massachusetts on Saturday in Foxborough, Mass.
Ely was intercepted three times in the first half, but the Rockets (7-0, 4-0 Mid-American Conference) rallied while he completed 26 of 47 passes for 355 yards.
Blake Frohnapfel completed 27 of 49 for 240 yards and four TDs for UMass (1-6, 0-3).
>> Get the most out of your Ohio State experience, follow @BuckeyeXtra on Twitter 
Buffalo 41, Ohio 17: Okezie Alozie returned one of his two interceptions for a touchdown to help host Buffalo (3-4, 1-2) beat Ohio (5-3, 2-2) in the MAC.
Buffalo picked off Derrius Vick three times and backup Greg Windham once. Ryan Williamson also returned an interception for a touchdown.
Vick was 32 of 51 for 321 yards.
>> Got a question about Ohio State football? Ask the experts! 
Bowling Green 48, Kent State 0: Matt Johnson passed for five touchdowns for the third consecutive game to lead visiting Bowling Green (6-2, 4-0) over Kent State (3-5, 2-2) in the MAC.
Pickerington Central grad Roger Lewis had 102 receiving yards and two scores for the Falcons, including a one-handed grab in the end zone and a 64-yarder in which he stole the ball from a defender.
Western Michigan 35, Miami 13: Zach Terrell threw for 278 yards and three TDs to lead host Western Michigan (4-3, 3-0) over Miami University (1-7, 0-4) in the MAC.
Cincinnati 37, Connecticut 13: Gunner Kiel, making his first start in a month because of a concussion, threw two touchdown passes and ran for a third to lead host Cincinnati (4-3, 1-2) over Connecticut (3-5, 1-3) in the American Athletic Conference.
Dayton 27, Butler 24: Tucker Yinger ran 50 yards for the go-ahead touchdown midway through the fourth quarter, then host Dayton (7-0, 4-0) held off Butler (4-3, 2-2) in the Pioneer League.
Southern Illinois 38, Youngstown State 31, OT: Mark Iannotti threw for 275 yards and three touchdowns — including the winner in overtime — to lead host Southern Illinois (3-4, 2-2) over Youngstown State (3-4, 1-3) in the Missouri Valley Conference.
Baldwin Wallace 55, Otterbein 21: Tyler Moeglin completed 20 of 23 passes for 276 yards and two touchdowns to lead visiting Baldwin Wallace (5-2, 5-1) over Otterbein (4-3, 4-2) in the Ohio Athletic Conference.
Kevan Green completed 23 of 37 passes for 237 yards and two touchdowns for Otterbein.
John Carroll 48, Capital 0: Jake Schaefer completed 17 of 25 passes for 331 yards and three touchdowns to lead visiting John Carroll (6-1, 5-1) over Capital (2-5, 2-4) in the OAC.
The Crusaders were held to 170 yards and allowed 604.
Denison 33, Allegheny 7: Freshman quarterback Canaan Gebele accounted for 283 yards and three touchdowns as visiting Denison (6-1, 5-1) pulled away from Allegheny (0-7, 0-6) in the North Coast Athletic Conference.
Gebele completed 17 of 24 passes for 143 yards and two touchdowns and ran 22 times for 140 yards and a score.
Ohio Wesleyan 27, DePauw 22: Brad Dotson returned an interception 32 yards for a touchdown and Jordan King brought back a punt 22 yards for a score to help Ohio Wesleyan (3-4, 3-3) surprise visiting DePauw (6-1, 5-1) in the NCAC.
Ohio Dominican 73, Quincy 28: Ohio Dominican (5-3) set a school record for points in a game in a nonconference win at Quincy (2-5). Darryl Johnson set a school record with five rushing TDs and also caught a touchdown pass, becoming the first ODU player with six touchdowns in a game.
